---
import DocsLayout from '../../layouts/DocsLayout.astro';
---

<DocsLayout title="Architecture overview" description="How Groundwork's two-tier token architecture is wired">
  <section class="gw-section">
    <div class="gw-width gw-stack--lg">
      <div class="gw-prose">
        <h1 class="gw-heading-l">Architecture overview</h1>
        <p>Groundwork uses two layers. Components reference semantic tokens only. Dark mode remaps semantic tokens to different primitives.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="gw-card gw-stack">
        <h2 class="gw-heading-m">Layer 1: primitives</h2>
        <p class="gw-body--sm">Private raw values prefixed <code class="gw-mono">--_gw-</code>: neutral scale, brand blue, status colours, spacing, type, borders, and radii.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="gw-card gw-stack">
        <h2 class="gw-heading-m">Layer 2: semantic tokens</h2>
        <p class="gw-body--sm">Public decisions such as <code class="gw-mono">--ink</code>, <code class="gw-mono">--surface-raised</code>, <code class="gw-mono">--action</code>, and <code class="gw-mono">--focus-ring-color</code>. Components are only allowed to reference these.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="gw-grid">
        <div class="gw-card gw-stack--sm"><span class="gw-caption">Ink</span><span class="gw-heading-s">--ink</span><p class="gw-body--sm">Primary text, headings, body.</p></div>
        <div class="gw-card gw-stack--sm"><span class="gw-caption">Surface</span><span class="gw-heading-s">--surface-raised</span><p class="gw-body--sm">Cards and elevated panels.</p></div>
        <div class="gw-card gw-stack--sm"><span class="gw-caption">Action</span><span class="gw-heading-s">--action</span><p class="gw-body--sm">Primary action colour.</p></div>
      </div>

      <div class="gw-prose">
        <p>Per-style tokens (colour, spacing, type, etc.) are surfaced inside the <a class="gw-link" href="/styles/">Styles</a> section alongside their usage guidance.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</DocsLayout>
